This paper is about recommender systems, which are commonly studied in the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also discusses metrics for measuring the coverage of long-tail items, which could fall under the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category. Additionally, the paper mentions regularization, which is a common technique in Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) and Cybersecurity (cs.CY).
